Protocol Definition

* Structure
** Request
Key                 Value
[to] // TBD
[from] // TBD

sessindID           <sessionID>
type                group
method              add | del | adduser | deluser | sendmsg | joinreq |\
                    quitreq | userlist | redmsg
params              (add)<Group ID> |
                    (del)<Group ID> |
                    (adduser)<User ID> |
                    (deluser)<User ID> |
                    (sendmsg)<User ID> <Newline> <Text> |
                    (joinreq)<User ID> <Newline> <GroupID> <Newline> <Text>|
                    (quitreq)<User ID> <Newline> <GroupID> |
                    (userlist)<Group ID> |
                    (redmsg)<Group ID> <Newline> <message>
                    /* <Newline> defines as UNIX style '\n' */

                    /* If not specified, just use the '\n'(as above) as the default parameter delimiter */
type                regular
method              login | logout | sendmsg | userlist | userinfo |\
                    add | modify | del | status
params              (login)<User ID> <PASSWD> |
                    (sendmsg)<User ID> <Text> |
                    (userinfo)<User ID> |
                    (add)<User Name> <PASSWD> <User Info> |
                    (modify)<User ID> <New Name> <New PASSWD> <New Phone> <User Info> |
                    (del)<User ID>


** Response
Key                 Value
userInfo            <User Info>
sessionID           <sessionID>
userList            <User ID> <User ID> ...
groupName           <Group Name>
groupID             <Group ID>

* Error Code
    SESSIONID_EXPECTED
    METHOD_EXPECTED
    TYPE_EXPECTED
    PARAMS_EXPECTED
    INVALID_METHOD
    INVALID_PARAMS
    INVALID_TYPE
    
